{"total": 16, "rows": [{"id": "gg6DcvBXEem1S2PcvINj5A", "created": "2019-10-16T20:57:04.546932+00:00", "updated": "2019-10-30T15:34:45.105612+00:00", "user": "acct:QDR@hypothes.is", "uri": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/5B7032EC65FE454D6B9B5B790634D3ED/S1531426X00002570a.pdf/grassroots_bureaucracy_intergovernmental_relations_and_popular_mobilization_in_brazils_aids_policy_sector.pdf", "text": "<a href=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/guidance/ati-at-a-glance\">\n<img src=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/drupal_data/public/ati_banner_long.png\" align=\"left\"/></a>\n<br>\n\n**Analytic Note:** This source is an internal government spreadsheet from 2010, containing a record of the number of parliamentary causes in Brazil and their locations. It was printed and given to me by the government bureaucrat who was in charge of the effort to promote parliamentary AIDS caucuses, Noemia Lima.\n\n**Data Source:** https://doi.org/10.5064/F6SF2T3N/ORR1S5\n\n**Full Citation:** Lima, Noemia. 2010. Bureaucrat, Department of Civil Society and Human Rights, Department of STD/AIDS, Ministry of Health. Author interview. Bras\u00edlia, March 19. ", "tags": [], "group": "2Nopp9mx", "permissions": {"read": ["group:__world__"], "admin": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "update": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "delete": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"]}, "target": [{"source": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/5B7032EC65FE454D6B9B5B790634D3ED/S1531426X00002570a.pdf/grassroots_bureaucracy_intergovernmental_relations_and_popular_mobilization_in_brazils_aids_policy_sector.pdf", "selector": [{"end": 56674, "type": "TextPositionSelector", "start": 56581}, {"type": "TextQuoteSelector", "exact": " such as the rural states of Amazonas and RioGrande do Norte (List of states\u2019 AIDS activism).", "prefix": "long histories of AIDS activism,", "suffix": "11Subnational AIDS caucuses have"}]}], "document": {"title": ["LAPS_Summer13"]}, "links": {"html": "https://hypothes.is/a/gg6DcvBXEem1S2PcvINj5A", "incontext": "https://hyp.is/gg6DcvBXEem1S2PcvINj5A/www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/5B7032EC65FE454D6B9B5B790634D3ED/S1531426X00002570a.pdf/grassroots_bureaucracy_intergovernmental_relations_and_popular_mobilization_in_brazils_aids_policy_sector.pdf", "json": "https://hypothes.is/api/annotations/gg6DcvBXEem1S2PcvINj5A"}, "flagged": false, "hidden": false, "user_info": {"display_name": "Qualitative Data Repository"}}, {"id": "jtTjJvBXEemqXkvcni6anw", "created": "2019-10-16T20:57:26.028280+00:00", "updated": "2019-10-30T15:23:21.082205+00:00", "user": "acct:QDR@hypothes.is", "uri": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/5B7032EC65FE454D6B9B5B790634D3ED/S1531426X00002570a.pdf/grassroots_bureaucracy_intergovernmental_relations_and_popular_mobilization_in_brazils_aids_policy_sector.pdf", "text": "<a href=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/guidance/ati-at-a-glance\">\n<img src=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/drupal_data/public/ati_banner_long.png\" align=\"left\"/></a>\n<br>\n\n**Analytic Note:** Here, I am including newspaper articles about the protests that I mention in my descriptive claim.\n\n**Data Source (All Sources):** https://doi.org/10.5064/F6SF2T3N/TZJWN2\n\n**Full Citation (Source 1):** Falta de rem\u00e9dio para HIV causa protestos. 2010. *Gazeta do Povo*, April 29.\n\n**Full Citation (Source 2):** Brasil: Falta de antirretrovirais gera protestos em sete estados brasileiros. 2010. Ag\u00eancia Lusa, April 28. \n\n**Full Citation (Source 3):** Falta de rem\u00e9dios contra aids causa protestos. 2010. *O Estado de S\u00e3o Paulo*, April 28. \n\n**Full Citation (Source 4):** Leite, Fabiane. Falta de rem\u00e9dios contra aids causa protestos. 2010. *O Estado de S\u00e3o Paulo*, April 28. ", "tags": [], "group": "2Nopp9mx", "permissions": {"read": ["group:__world__"], "admin": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "update": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "delete": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"]}, "target": [{"source": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/5B7032EC65FE454D6B9B5B790634D3ED/S1531426X00002570a.pdf/grassroots_bureaucracy_intergovernmental_relations_and_popular_mobilization_in_brazils_aids_policy_sector.pdf", "selector": [{"end": 57290, "type": "TextPositionSelector", "start": 57205}, {"type": "TextQuoteSelector", "exact": "AIDS net-works in the Northeastern states of Maranh\u00e3o, Pernambuco, Cear\u00e1, and Para\u00edba", "prefix": "ulo and Rio de Janeiro but also ", "suffix": ".Qualitative interviews provide "}]}], "document": {"title": ["LAPS_Summer13"]}, "links": {"html": "https://hypothes.is/a/jtTjJvBXEemqXkvcni6anw", "incontext": "https://hyp.is/jtTjJvBXEemqXkvcni6anw/www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/5B7032EC65FE454D6B9B5B790634D3ED/S1531426X00002570a.pdf/grassroots_bureaucracy_intergovernmental_relations_and_popular_mobilization_in_brazils_aids_policy_sector.pdf", "json": "https://hypothes.is/api/annotations/jtTjJvBXEemqXkvcni6anw"}, "flagged": false, "hidden": false, "user_info": {"display_name": "Qualitative Data Repository"}}, {"id": "dfBvdPBXEemhtM9gdrHytA", "created": "2019-10-16T20:56:44.250852+00:00", "updated": "2019-10-30T15:17:57.866384+00:00", "user": "acct:QDR@hypothes.is", "uri": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/5B7032EC65FE454D6B9B5B790634D3ED/S1531426X00002570a.pdf/grassroots_bureaucracy_intergovernmental_relations_and_popular_mobilization_in_brazils_aids_policy_sector.pdf", "text": "<a href=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/guidance/ati-at-a-glance\">\n<img src=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/drupal_data/public/ati_banner_long.png\" align=\"left\"/></a>\n<br>\n\n**Analytic Note:** I substantiate this claim in the book manuscript but not in this article, due to space constraints, and because the claim is not central to main my argument. Nevertheless, I am including here a document containing notes from my 2011 interview with Rubens Duda, as direct evidence to support the claim. The interview notes are sparse and not particularly clear. However, the interview recording from Minute 20 to Minute 30-something, provides clear and direct evidence in support of my in-text claim. In it, Rubens Duda describes how the national AIDS program helped activists form state-wide AIDS advocacy networks in new states of Brazil. It was an effort led by the AIDS advocacy networks in Rio and S\u00e3o Paulo, and the national AIDS program support the efforts of these activists from Rio and S\u00e3o Paulo with funding and by traveling to different states of Brazil to help advertise and explain the concept of an AIDS advocacy network (referred to as \u201cforums\u201d).\n\n**Data Source:** https://doi.org/10.5064/F6SF2T3N/MLRJUI\n\n**Full Citation:** Duda, Rubens. 2011. Bureaucrat, Department of Civil Society and Human Rights, Department of STD/AIDS, Ministry of Health. Author interview. August 24.", "tags": [], "group": "2Nopp9mx", "permissions": {"read": ["group:__world__"], "admin": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "update": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "delete": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"]}, "target": [{"source": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/5B7032EC65FE454D6B9B5B790634D3ED/S1531426X00002570a.pdf/grassroots_bureaucracy_intergovernmental_relations_and_popular_mobilization_in_brazils_aids_policy_sector.pdf", "selector": [{"end": 54356, "type": "TextPositionSelector", "start": 54259}, {"type": "TextQuoteSelector", "exact": "21 percent of survey respondents received over 75percent of their budgets from government funding", "prefix": "etsfrom government funding; and ", "suffix": ".Federal efforts to support coll"}]}], "document": {"title": ["LAPS_Summer13"]}, "links": {"html": "https://hypothes.is/a/dfBvdPBXEemhtM9gdrHytA", "incontext": "https://hyp.is/dfBvdPBXEemhtM9gdrHytA/www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/5B7032EC65FE454D6B9B5B790634D3ED/S1531426X00002570a.pdf/grassroots_bureaucracy_intergovernmental_relations_and_popular_mobilization_in_brazils_aids_policy_sector.pdf", "json": "https://hypothes.is/api/annotations/dfBvdPBXEemhtM9gdrHytA"}, "flagged": false, "hidden": false, "user_info": {"display_name": "Qualitative Data Repository"}}, {"id": "bnXdTPBXEempFEMpwlc43g", "created": "2019-10-16T20:56:31.706695+00:00", "updated": "2019-10-30T15:16:02.042891+00:00", "user": "acct:QDR@hypothes.is", "uri": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/5B7032EC65FE454D6B9B5B790634D3ED/S1531426X00002570a.pdf/grassroots_bureaucracy_intergovernmental_relations_and_popular_mobilization_in_brazils_aids_policy_sector.pdf", "text": "<a href=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/guidance/ati-at-a-glance\">\n<img src=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/drupal_data/public/ati_banner_long.png\" align=\"left\"/></a>\n<br>\n\n**Analytic Note:** This document is a national catalog of civil society organizations working with AIDS in 2003. It constitutes an attempt by the national AIDS bureaucracy to collect data on AIDS NGOs in Brazil. I built my own national database of AIDS NGOs in 2003 to use for analysis, and I did it using the data contained within this catalog.\n\n**Data Source:** https://doi.org/10.5064/F6SF2T3N/SH7G9F\n\n**Full Citation:** Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade. 2003. Cat\u00e1logo de organiza\u00e7\u00f5es da sociedade civil HIV/AIDS 2001/2002. Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade. ", "tags": [], "group": "2Nopp9mx", "permissions": {"read": ["group:__world__"], "admin": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "update": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "delete": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"]}, "target": [{"source": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/5B7032EC65FE454D6B9B5B790634D3ED/S1531426X00002570a.pdf/grassroots_bureaucracy_intergovernmental_relations_and_popular_mobilization_in_brazils_aids_policy_sector.pdf", "selector": [{"end": 52931, "type": "TextPositionSelector", "start": 52845}, {"type": "TextQuoteSelector", "exact": "associations in the North and Northwest regions received fundingfrom federal contracts", "prefix": "me. The vast major-ity of these ", "suffix": " (Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade 2003). Mor"}]}], "document": {"title": ["LAPS_Summer13"]}, "links": {"html": "https://hypothes.is/a/bnXdTPBXEempFEMpwlc43g", "incontext": "https://hyp.is/bnXdTPBXEempFEMpwlc43g/www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/5B7032EC65FE454D6B9B5B790634D3ED/S1531426X00002570a.pdf/grassroots_bureaucracy_intergovernmental_relations_and_popular_mobilization_in_brazils_aids_policy_sector.pdf", "json": "https://hypothes.is/api/annotations/bnXdTPBXEempFEMpwlc43g"}, "flagged": false, "hidden": false, "user_info": {"display_name": "Qualitative Data Repository"}}, {"id": "ZLzmavBXEemq88dCLGrE2Q", "created": "2019-10-16T20:56:15.388980+00:00", "updated": "2019-10-30T14:59:52.528470+00:00", "user": "acct:QDR@hypothes.is", "uri": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/5B7032EC65FE454D6B9B5B790634D3ED/S1531426X00002570a.pdf/grassroots_bureaucracy_intergovernmental_relations_and_popular_mobilization_in_brazils_aids_policy_sector.pdf", "text": "<a href=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/guidance/ati-at-a-glance\">\n<img src=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/drupal_data/public/ati_banner_long.png\" align=\"left\"/></a>\n<br>\n\n**Analytic Note:** This document is a national catalog of civil society organizations working with AIDS in 2003. It constitutes an attempt by the national AIDS bureaucracy to collect data on AIDS NGOs in Brazil. I built my own national database of AIDS NGOs in 2003 to use for analysis, and I did it using the data contained within this catalog.\n\n**Data Source:** https://doi.org/10.5064/F6SF2T3N/SH7G9F\n\n**Full Citation:** Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade. 2003. Cat\u00e1logo de organiza\u00e7\u00f5es da sociedade civil HIV/AIDS 2001/2002. Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade. ", "tags": [], "group": "2Nopp9mx", "permissions": {"read": ["group:__world__"], "admin": ["acct:QDR@hypothe