acy in the year 2007. Pages 7-9 contain data on groups that received legal aid \u201cassessoria juridica\u201d project funding. I tallied the total number of recipient organizations and also counted the number of recipient organizations per geographic region.\n\n**Data Source:** https://doi.org/10.5064/F6SF2T3N/YZKTTN\n\n**Full Citation:** Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade. National AIDS Program. n.d. List of states\u2019 AIDS activism. Unpublished internal document.\n", "tags": [], "group": "2Nopp9mx", "permissions": {"read": ["group:__world__"], "admin": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "update": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "delete": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"]}, "target": [{"source": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/5B7032EC65FE454D6B9B5B790634D3ED/S1531426X00002570a.pdf/grassroots_bureaucracy_intergovernmental_relations_and_popular_mobilization_in_brazils_aids_policy_sector.pdf", "selector": [{"end": 34300, "type": "TextPositionSelector", "start": 34227}, {"type": "TextQuoteSelector", "exact": "a region notorious forhuman rights violations and gender-related violence", "prefix": "funded groups in the Northeast, ", "suffix": " (unpublished governmentdocument"}]}], "document": {"title": ["LAPS_Summer13"]}, "links": {"html": "https://hypothes.is/a/KUudBvBXEemQ6B9ak1QIdA", "incontext": "https://hyp.is/KUudBvBXEemQ6B9ak1QIdA/www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/5B7032EC65FE454D6B9B5B790634D3ED/S1531426X00002570a.pdf/grassroots_bureaucracy_intergovernmental_relations_and_popular_mobilization_in_brazils_aids_policy_sector.pdf", "json": "https://hypothes.is/api/annotations/KUudBvBXEemQ6B9ak1QIdA"}, "flagged": false, "hidden": false, "user_info": {"display_name": "Qualitative Data Repository"}}, {"id": "QkM4qvBXEem9jSOT9wJ-xw", "created": "2019-10-16T20:55:17.541543+00:00", "updated": "2019-10-30T14:56:18.128424+00:00", "user": "acct:QDR@hypothes.is", "uri": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/5B7032EC65FE454D6B9B5B790634D3ED/S1531426X00002570a.pdf/grassroots_bureaucracy_intergovernmental_relations_and_popular_mobilization_in_brazils_aids_policy_sector.pdf", "text": "<a href=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/guidance/ati-at-a-glance\">\n<img src=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/drupal_data/public/ati_banner_long.png\" align=\"left\"/></a>\n<br>\n\n**Data Source:** https://doi.org/10.5064/F6SF2T3N/SUWANP\n\n**Full Citation:** Duda, Rubens. 2010. Bureaucrat, Department of Civil Society and Human Rights, Department of STD/AIDS, Ministry of Health. Author interview. Bras\u00edlia, March 18.", "tags": [], "group": "2Nopp9mx", "permissions": {"read": ["group:__world__"], "admin": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "update": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "delete": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"]}, "target": [{"source": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/5B7032EC65FE454D6B9B5B790634D3ED/S1531426X00002570a.pdf/grassroots_bureaucracy_intergovernmental_relations_and_popular_mobilization_in_brazils_aids_policy_sector.pdf", "selector": [{"end": 49236, "type": "TextPositionSelector", "start": 49124}, {"type": "TextQuoteSelector", "exact": "in fights between states and municipalities, between [civil society]organizations and the municipality or state\u201d", "prefix": "ent [local] groups; forexample, ", "suffix": " (Duda 2010).Federal bureaucrats"}]}], "document": {"title": ["LAPS_Summer13"]}, "links": {"html": "https://hypothes.is/a/QkM4qvBXEem9jSOT9wJ-xw", "incontext": "https://hyp.is/QkM4qvBXEem9jSOT9wJ-xw/www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/5B7032EC65FE454D6B9B5B790634D3ED/S1531426X00002570a.pdf/grassroots_bureaucracy_intergovernmental_relations_and_popular_mobilization_in_brazils_aids_policy_sector.pdf", "json": "https://hypothes.is/api/annotations/QkM4qvBXEem9jSOT9wJ-xw"}, "flagged": false, "hidden": false, "user_info": {"display_name": "Qualitative Data Repository"}}, {"id": "Nm93bvBXEem0EbN3o9f1HA", "created": "2019-10-16T20:54:57.709448+00:00", "updated": "2019-10-30T14:54:56.951499+00:00", "user": "acct:QDR@hypothes.is", "uri": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/5B7032EC65FE454D6B9B5B790634D3ED/S1531426X00002570a.pdf/grassroots_bureaucracy_intergovernmental_relations_and_popular_mobilization_in_brazils_aids_policy_sector.pdf", "text": "<a href=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/guidance/ati-at-a-glance\">\n<img src=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/drupal_data/public/ati_banner_long.png\" align=\"left\"/></a>\n<br>\n\n**Analytic Note:** This document is the original set of bylaws of the National Council of Articulation with Social Movements (CASM). The link provided here contains not only the bylaws but also the minutes of every CASM meeting since its inauguration in January 2004.\n\n**Data Source:** https://doi.org/10.5064/F6SF2T3N/AT1DJQ\n\n**Full Citation:** National Council of Articulation with Social Movements (CASM). 2004-9. Minutes of meetings.", "tags": [], "group": "2Nopp9mx", "permissions": {"read": ["group:__world__"], "admin": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "update": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "delete": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"]}, "target": [{"source": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/5B7032EC65FE454D6B9B5B790634D3ED/S1531426X00002570a.pdf/grassroots_bureaucracy_intergovernmental_relations_and_popular_mobilization_in_brazils_aids_policy_sector.pdf", "selector": [{"end": 41957, "type": "TextPositionSelector", "start": 41898}, {"type": "TextQuoteSelector", "exact": "\u201cin the context of a decentralized national health system\u201d ", "prefix": "razil\u2019s national AIDSpolicies]\u201d ", "suffix": "(CASM 2004).Moreover, a review o"}]}], "document": {"title": ["LAPS_Summer13"]}, "links": {"html": "https://hypothes.is/a/Nm93bvBXEem0EbN3o9f1HA", "incontext": "https://hyp.is/Nm93bvBXEem0EbN3o9f1HA/www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/5B7032EC65FE454D6B9B5B790634D3ED/S1531426X00002570a.pdf/grassroots_bureaucracy_intergovernmental_relations_and_popular_mobilization_in_brazils_aids_policy_sector.pdf", "json": "https://hypothes.is/api/annotations/Nm93bvBXEem0EbN3o9f1HA"}, "flagged": false, "hidden": false, "user_info": {"display_name": "Qualitative Data Repository"}}, {"id": "AmU4MvBXEemssf_MwIuyGw", "created": "2019-10-16T20:53:30.408455+00:00", "updated": "2019-10-30T14:46:21.002800+00:00", "user": "acct:QDR@hypothes.is", "uri": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/5B7032EC65FE454D6B9B5B790634D3ED/S1531426X00002570a.pdf/grassroots_bureaucracy_intergovernmental_relations_and_popular_mobilization_in_brazils_aids_policy_sector.pdf", "text": "<a href=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/guidance/ati-at-a-glance\">\n<img src=\"https://qdr.syr.edu/drupal_data/public/ati_banner_long.png\" align=\"left\"/></a>\n<br>\n\n**Analytic Note:** In drawing up Table 1, I used the information in CSHR 2006, the national budget for civil-society funding. Because I am interested in money that national bureaucrats give directly to civil society organizations, I deleted the two line items that entailed targeted transfers to state-level governments (items 1 and 2 on the budget, which I know are funds that are distributed to civil society groups by state-level governments through my numerous interviews and analysis of other government documents). I also relabeled the categories for clarity.\n\n**Data Source:** https://doi.org/10.5064/F6SF2T3N/GSLM3G\n\n**Full Citation:** Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade. National AIDS Program. Civil Society and Human Rights sector (CSHR). 2006. Exerc\u00edcio 2006. Unpublished government document. Accessed August 28, 2006.", "tags": [], "group": "2Nopp9mx", "permissions": {"read": ["group:__world__"], "admin": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "update": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"], "delete": ["acct:QDR@hypothes.is"]}, "target": [{"source": "https://www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/5B7032EC65FE454D6B9B5B790634D3ED/S1531426X0